1	Acetazolamide	carbonic anhydrase inhibitor,diuretic,glaucoma,epilepsy	Acetazolamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor used primarily to treat glaucoma, epilepsy (as an adjunct), and altitude sickness. It also acts as a diuretic to reduce fluid retention and is sometimes used for periodic paralysis and idiopathic intracranial hypertension.
2	Acetylcysteine	mucolytic,antidote,paracetamol overdose,antioxidant	Acetylcysteine is a mucolytic agent that breaks down mucus in respiratory conditions like cystic fibrosis and COPD. It is also a life-saving antidote for paracetamol (acetaminophen) overdose, preventing hepatotoxicity by replenishing glutathione levels.
3	Acetylsalicylic Acid	NSAID,antiplatelet,analgesic,antipyretic,aspirin	Acetylsalicylic Acid (Aspirin) is a non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug used as an analgesic for mild pain, an antipyretic for fever, and an antiplatelet agent for preventing heart attacks, strokes, and blood clots in high-risk patients.
4	Actinomycin D	chemotherapy,antibiotic,antineoplastic,pediatric cancer	Actinomycin D is a chemotherapy agent used to treat various cancers including Wilms' tumor, Ewing's sarcoma, gestational trophoblastic neoplasia, and rhabdomyosarcoma. It works by intercalating DNA and inhibiting RNA synthesis.
5	Activated Charcoal	antidote,adsorbent,poisoning,overdose,emergency	Activated Charcoal is an emergency antidote used to treat poisonings and drug overdoses by adsorbing toxins in the gastrointestinal tract, preventing their systemic absorption. It is most effective within one hour of ingestion.
6	Acyclovir	antiviral,herpes,shingles,chickenpox,HSV	Acyclovir is an antiviral medication used to treat infections caused by herpes simplex virus (HSV) including genital herpes, cold sores, and herpes encephalitis, as well as varicella-zoster virus causing chickenpox and shingles.
7	Adrenaline	vasoconstrictor,anaphylaxis,catecholamine,emergency,cardiac arrest	Adrenaline (Epinephrine) is a hormone and medication used for anaphylaxis, cardiac arrest, and severe asthma attacks. It works by constricting blood vessels, relaxing airway muscles, and increasing heart rate.
8	Adriamycin	chemotherapy,anthracycline,antineoplastic,breast cancer	Adriamycin (Doxorubicin) is an anthracycline chemotherapy agent used to treat breast cancer, bladder cancer, lymphoma, leukemia, and many other solid tumors. It works by intercalating DNA and inhibiting topoisomerase II.
9	Albendazole	anthelmintic,antiparasitic,worm infection,hydatid disease	Albendazole is a broad-spectrum anthelmintic used to treat intestinal worm infections including roundworm, hookworm, whipworm, pinworm, and tapeworms. It is also effective against neurocysticercosis and hydatid disease.
10	Allopurinol	xanthine oxidase inhibitor,gout,hyperuricemia,uric acid	Allopurinol is a xanthine oxidase inhibitor used to prevent gout attacks and treat hyperuricemia by reducing uric acid production. It is also used for tumor lysis syndrome and recurrent calcium kidney stones.
11	Amino Acid Solution	nutrition,TPN,parenteral nutrition,intravenous,protein	Amino Acid Solution is a sterile intravenous preparation used for total parenteral nutrition (TPN) in patients who cannot obtain adequate nutrition through enteral routes. It provides essential and non-essential amino acids for protein synthesis.
12	Aminophylline	bronchodilator,theophylline,asthma,COPD,respiratory	Aminophylline is a bronchodilator containing theophylline used to treat asthma, COPD, and other respiratory conditions. It relaxes airway smooth muscles and improves diaphragmatic contractility.
