15	Amlodipine	calcium channel blocker,antihypertensive,angina,vasodilator	Amlodipine is a long-acting calcium channel blocker used to treat hypertension and coronary artery disease including chronic stable angina and vasospastic angina. It works by relaxing blood vessels.
16	Amodiaquine + Artesunate	antimalarial,combination therapy,ACT,Plasmodium falciparum	Amodiaquine + Artesunate is an artemisinin-based combination therapy (ACT) used to treat uncomplicated malaria caused by Plasmodium falciparum. The combination reduces parasite burden and prevents drug resistance.
