31	Atropine	anticholinergic,muscarinic antagonist,bradycardia,antidote,mydriatic	Atropine is a muscarinic acetylcholine antagonist used to treat bradycardia, as an antidote for organophosphate poisoning, and as a preoperative medication to reduce secretions. It also causes pupil dilation.
