193	Miconazole	antifungal,azole,topical,vaginal,candidiasis,dermatophyte	Miconazole is an azole antifungal used topically for fungal skin infections (athlete's foot, ringworm, jock itch, tinea versicolor) and for vaginal yeast infections (candidiasis).
194	Midazolam	benzodiazepine,sedative,anxiolytic,preoperative,status epilepticus	Midazolam is a short-acting benzodiazepine used for preoperative sedation (conscious sedation), induction of anesthesia, treatment of status epilepticus, and for procedural sedation.
195	Morphine	opioid,analgesic,severe pain,postoperative,narcotic	Morphine is a potent opioid analgesic used to treat severe acute and chronic pain, including postoperative pain, cancer pain, and pain from myocardial infarction. It acts on mu-opioid receptors in the central nervous system.
196	Morphine Sulphate	opioid,analgesic,slow release,severe pain,narcotic	Morphine Sulphate is the sulfate salt of morphine, available in immediate and sustained-release formulations for treating moderate to severe pain. The slow-release version provides around-the-clock pain relief.
197	Multivitamin	vitamin supplement,nutrition,micronutrient,dietary supplement	Multivitamins are combination supplements containing various vitamins and minerals used to prevent or treat nutritional deficiencies when diet alone is insufficient. They support overall health and metabolic functions.
198	Naloxone	opioid antagonist,antidote,overdose,emergency,naltrexone	Naloxone (Narcan) is an opioid antagonist used to rapidly reverse opioid overdose (heroin, morphine, fentanyl). It binds to opioid receptors, displacing opioids and reversing respiratory depression.
199	Neomycin	antibiotic,aminoglycoside,topical,oral,hepatic encephalopathy	Neomycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic used topically for skin infections and orally to reduce intestinal bacteria before surgery and to treat hepatic encephalopathy by reducing ammonia-producing bacteria.
200	Neostigmine Bromide	cholinesterase inhibitor,myasthenia gravis,postoperative ileus	Neostigmine Bromide is a cholinesterase inhibitor used to treat myasthenia gravis, reverse neuromuscular blockade after surgery, and treat postoperative ileus (paralytic ileus) and urinary retention.
201	Neostigmine	cholinesterase inhibitor,myasthenia gravis,reversal agent	Neostigmine is a cholinesterase inhibitor used to treat myasthenia gravis and to reverse the effects of non-depolarizing neuromuscular blocking agents after surgery.
202	Nifedipine	calcium channel blocker,antihypertensive,angina,vasodilator	Nifedipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker used to treat hypertension and angina pectoris (chronic stable angina and vasospastic angina). It causes potent arterial vasodilation.
203	Nitrofurantoin	antibiotic,UTI,urinary tract infection,antibacterial	Nitrofurantoin is a urinary tract antibiotic used specifically to treat and prevent uncomplicated lower urinary tract infections (cystitis) caused by susceptible bacteria like E. coli.
204	Norethisterone	progestin,contraception,endometriosis,abnormal bleeding	Norethisterone (Norethindrone) is a progestin used for contraception, endometriosis, abnormal uterine bleeding, and as a component of hormone replacement therapy. It can also delay menstruation.
205	Nystatin	antifungal,polyene,candidiasis,topical,oral,thrush	Nystatin is a polyene antifungal used to treat Candida (yeast) infections including oral thrush, vaginal yeast infections, and cutaneous candidiasis. It is poorly absorbed and acts topically.
206	Olanzapine	antipsychotic,atypical,schizophrenia,bipolar,serotonin-dopamine antagonist	Olanzapine is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat schizophrenia, bipolar disorder (mania and maintenance), and treatment-resistant depression. It blocks multiple neurotransmitter receptors including dopamine D2 and serotonin 5-HT2A.
207	Omeprazole	proton pump inhibitor,PPI,acid reducer,GERD,ulcer	Omeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor used to treat GERD, gastric and duodenal ulcers, Zollinger-Ellison syndrome, and as part of Helicobacter pylori eradication therapy. It blocks gastric acid production.
208	Ondansetrone	antiemetic,5-HT3 antagonist,chemotherapy,nausea,vomiting	Ondansetron is a 5-HT3 receptor antagonist used to prevent and treat nausea and vomiting caused by chemotherapy, radiation therapy, and surgery (postoperative nausea and vomiting).
209	Oral Rehydration Salts	ORS,electrolyte replacement,dehydration,diarrhea,cholera	Oral Rehydration Salts (ORS) are a specific formulation of glucose and electrolytes (sodium, potassium, chloride, citrate) used to treat and prevent dehydration from diarrhea, vomiting, and cholera, especially in children.
210	Oxytocin	hormone,uterotonic,postpartum hemorrhage,labor induction	Oxytocin is a hormone used to induce or augment labor, control postpartum hemorrhage by causing uterine contraction, and to facilitate breast milk ejection (let-down reflex).
211	Paclitaxel	chemotherapy,taxane,antineoplastic,breast cancer,ovarian cancer	Paclitaxel is a taxane chemotherapy agent used to treat breast cancer, ovarian cancer, lung cancer, and Kaposi's sarcoma. It stabilizes microtubules, preventing cell division.
212	Paracetamol	analgesic,antipyretic,acetaminophen,pain,fever	Paracetamol (Acetaminophen) is an analgesic and antipyretic used to treat mild to moderate pain (headache, dental pain, muscle aches) and fever. It has weak anti-inflammatory effects and is safe in children.
213	Paraffin	emollient,laxative,lubricant,skin protectant,mineral oil	Paraffin (Liquid Paraffin, Mineral Oil) is used as a lubricant laxative for constipation and as an emollient in skin care products to soften and protect dry skin.
214	Pethidine	opioid,analgesic,meperidine,postoperative pain,labor pain	Pethidine (Meperidine) is an opioid analgesic used to treat moderate to severe pain, including postoperative pain, labor pain, and renal colic. It has anticholinergic and spasmolytic properties.
215	Phenobarbital	barbiturate,anticonvulsant,sedative,epilepsy,status epilepticus	Phenobarbital is a long-acting barbiturate used as an anticonvulsant for all forms of epilepsy (including status epilepticus) and as a sedative/hypnotic, though it is less commonly used for sedation now.
216	Phenol	antiseptic,disinfectant,sclerosing agent,topical	Phenol is used as a topical antiseptic and disinfectant. In medical procedures, it is used as a sclerosing agent for varicose veins and for chemical matrixectomy for ingrown toenails.
217	Phenoxymethyl Penicillin	antibiotic,penicillin,oral,streptococcus,gram-positive	Phenoxymethyl Penicillin (Penicillin V) is an oral penicillin antibiotic used to treat mild to moderate infections caused by streptococci and other susceptible gram-positive bacteria, including pharyngitis, tonsillitis, and skin infections.
218	Phenytoin	anticonvulsant,seizures,epilepsy,status epilepticus,arrhythmia	Phenytoin is an anticonvulsant used to treat generalized tonic-clonic seizures and partial seizures. It can also be used for status epilepticus (IV) and certain cardiac arrhythmias.
219	Phenytoin Sodium	anticonvulsant,sodium channel blocker,epilepsy,seizures	Phenytoin Sodium is the sodium salt form of phenytoin, an anticonvulsant used for tonic-clonic and partial seizures, and for status epilepticus (administered intravenously).
220	Phytomenadione	vitamin K,coagulation,antidote,warfarin reversal,newborn	Phytomenadione (Vitamin K1) is used to reverse warfarin (coumarin) anticoagulation and to prevent and treat vitamin K deficiency bleeding (hemorrhagic disease) in newborns.
221	Pilocarpine	muscarinic agonist,glaucoma,Sjogren's,cholinergic,miotic	Pilocarpine is a muscarinic cholinergic agonist used as eye drops to reduce intraocular pressure in glaucoma and ocular hypertension. Orally, it is used to treat dry mouth in Sjogren's syndrome and after radiation therapy.
222	Pioglitazone	thiazolidinedione,TZD,antidiabetic,insulin sensitizer,type 2	Pioglitazone is a thiazolidinedione used to treat type 2 diabetes. It improves insulin sensitivity by activating PPAR-gamma receptors, increasing glucose uptake in fat and muscle.
223	Piracetam	nootropic,cognitive enhancer,myoclonus,racetam	Piracetam is a nootropic (cognitive enhancer) used in some countries to treat myoclonus and cognitive impairment. It is believed to improve brain function by modulating neurotransmitters and enhancing membrane fluidity.
224	Potassium Chloride	electrolyte,potassium supplement,hypokalemia,IV,oral	Potassium Chloride is used to prevent and treat hypokalemia (low potassium levels) caused by diuretics, vomiting, diarrhea, or other conditions. It is administered orally or intravenously.
225	Potassium Citrate	alkalinizing agent,urinary alkalinizer,uric acid stones,kidney stones	Potassium Citrate is used to alkalinize urine, preventing the formation of uric acid and cystine kidney stones. It is also used to treat metabolic acidosis.
226	Povidone Iodine	antiseptic,disinfectant,surgical scrub,wound care,topical	Povidone Iodine (Betadine) is a broad-spectrum antiseptic used for surgical skin preparation, wound cleansing, and treating minor skin infections. It kills bacteria, fungi, viruses, and protozoa.
227	Praziquantel	anthelmintic,squistosomiasis,tapeworm,flatworm,fluke	Praziquantel is an anthelmintic used to treat infections caused by schistosomes (schistosomiasis), liver flukes, and tapeworms (including neurocysticercosis). It increases parasite cell membrane permeability to calcium.
228	Prazosin	alpha blocker,alpha-1 antagonist,hypertension,BPH,PTSD	Prazosin is an alpha-1 adrenergic antagonist used to treat hypertension and benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). It is also used off-label for nightmares associated with PTSD.
229	Prednisolone	corticosteroid,glucocorticoid,anti-inflammatory,immunosuppressant	Prednisolone is a glucocorticoid used to treat various inflammatory and autoimmune conditions including asthma, allergic reactions, rheumatoid arthritis, ulcerative colitis, and nephrotic syndrome.
230	Primidone	anticonvulsant,barbiturate,epilepsy,essential tremor	Primidone is an anticonvulsant (related to phenobarbital) used to treat various seizure types including generalized tonic-clonic and partial seizures, and for essential tremor.
231	Procaine Benzylpenicillin	antibiotic,penicillin,procaine,depot,benzathine	Procaine Benzylpenicillin is a depot form of penicillin G used for streptococcal infections, syphilis, and as prophylaxis against rheumatic fever. It provides sustained release of penicillin.
232	Promethazine Hydrochloride	antihistamine,first generation,antiemetic,sedative,motion sickness	Promethazine Hydrochloride is a first-generation antihistamine used for allergic reactions, as an antiemetic (nausea/vomiting), for motion sickness, and as a sedative/preoperative medication.
233	Promethazine Theoclate	antihistamine,antiemetic,motion sickness,nausea,first generation	Promethazine Theoclate (Promethazine Teoclate) is a first-generation antihistamine and antiemetic specifically used to prevent and treat motion sickness, nausea, and vomiting.
234	Propranolol	beta blocker,non-selective,antihypertensive,migraine,anxiety	Propranolol is a non-selective beta-adrenergic antagonist used for hypertension, angina, migraine prevention, anxiety (performance anxiety), essential tremor, and thyrotoxicosis.
235	Propylthiouracil	antithyroid,hyperthyroidism,Graves' disease,thyroid inhibitor	Propylthiouracil (PTU) is an antithyroid medication used to treat hyperthyroidism (Graves' disease). It inhibits thyroid peroxidase and also blocks peripheral conversion of T4 to T3.
236	Protamine Sulphate	anticoagulant reversal,heparin antagonist,protamine	Protamine Sulphate is used to reverse the anticoagulant effects of heparin. It binds to heparin, forming a stable complex that neutralizes its activity, and is used after cardiac surgery or heparin overdose.
237	Quinine	antimalarial,muscle cramp,Plasmodium,cinchona	Quinine is an antimalarial used to treat uncomplicated malaria caused by chloroquine-resistant Plasmodium falciparum. It is also used to treat nocturnal leg muscle cramps.
238	Ramipril	ACE inhibitor,antihypertensive,heart failure,cardiovascular	Ramipril is an ACE inhibitor used to treat hypertension, heart failure, and to reduce cardiovascular events (heart attack, stroke) in high-risk patients. It blocks angiotensin II formation.
239	Ranitidine	H2 antagonist,acid reducer,ulcer,GERD,dyspepsia	Ranitidine is an H2 receptor antagonist used to treat peptic ulcers, GERD, and Zollinger-Ellison syndrome. It reduces gastric acid secretion by blocking histamine receptors on parietal cells.
240	Retinol	vitamin A,retinoid,skin care,acne,antioxidant	Retinol (Vitamin A) is used as a dietary supplement to prevent and treat vitamin A deficiency. Topically, it is used for acne and photoaging, promoting skin cell turnover and collagen production.
241	Ringer - Lactate Solution	intravenous fluid,electrolyte,hydration,resuscitation,isotonic	Ringer-Lactate Solution (Hartmann's Solution) is an isotonic intravenous fluid containing sodium, potassium, calcium, chloride, and lactate. It is used for fluid resuscitation, dehydration, and metabolic acidosis.
242	Risperidone	antipsychotic,atypical,schizophrenia,bipolar,autism	Risperidone is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat schizophrenia, bipolar disorder (mania), irritability associated with autism, and other psychiatric conditions. It blocks dopamine D2 and serotonin 5-HT2A receptors.
243	Rituximab	monoclonal antibody,CD20,chemotherapy,lymphoma,autoimmune	Rituximab is a monoclonal antibody that targets CD20 on B-cells. It is used to treat non-Hodgkin lymphoma, chronic lymphocytic leukemia, rheumatoid arthritis, and other autoimmune diseases (e.g., vasculitis, lupus).
244	Salbutamol	bronchodilator,beta-2 agonist,asthma,COPD,reliever	Salbutamol (Albuterol) is a short-acting beta-2 adrenergic agonist used as a bronchodilator for asthma and COPD. It provides rapid relief of bronchospasm in acute attacks.
245	Salbutamol Sulphate	bronchodilator,beta-2 agonist,asthma,COPD,inhaler	Salbutamol Sulphate is the sulfate salt of salbutamol, a short-acting beta-2 agonist bronchodilator used for acute relief of bronchospasm in asthma and COPD.
246	Salicylic Acid	keratolytic,topical,acne,wart,psoriasis	Salicylic Acid is a keratolytic agent used topically to treat acne, warts, corns, calluses, and psoriasis. It works by softening keratin and promoting shedding of the outer skin layer.
247	Secnidazole	antiprotozoal,nitroimidazole,trichomoniasis,bacterial vaginosis	Secnidazole is a nitroimidazole antiprotozoal used to treat trichomoniasis, bacterial vaginosis, and intestinal amebiasis. It has a longer half-life than metronidazole, allowing single-dose therapy.
248	Selenium Sulphide	antifungal,seborrheic dermatitis,dandruff,topical	Selenium Sulphide is a topical antifungal used to treat seborrheic dermatitis (dandruff), tinea versicolor (pityriasis versicolor), and other fungal skin infections.
249	Sertraline	SSRI,antidepressant,anxiety,PTSD,OCD,panic	Sertraline is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) used to treat major depression, panic disorder, OCD, PTSD, social anxiety disorder, and premenstrual dysphoric disorder (PMDD).
250	Silver Sulphadiazine	topical antibiotic,burn cream,antibacterial,wound care	Silver Sulphadiazine is a topical antibiotic cream used to prevent and treat infection in second and third-degree burns. It has broad-spectrum antibacterial activity including against Pseudomonas.
251	Simple Linctus BPC	cough suppressant,dry cough,demulcent,OTC	Simple Linctus BPC (British Pharmaceutical Codex) is a simple cough syrup containing a demulcent (usually glycerin or syrup) used to relieve dry, irritating coughs.
252	Simvastatin	statin,HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor,cholesterol,lipid lowering	Simvastatin is a statin medication used to lower cholesterol and triglyceride levels, reducing cardiovascular risk. It inhibits HMG-CoA reductase, the rate-limiting enzyme in cholesterol synthesis.
253	Sodium Bicarbonate	alkalinizing agent,antacid,metabolic acidosis,IV,oral	Sodium Bicarbonate is used to treat metabolic acidosis, as an antacid for heartburn, and to alkalinize urine. Intravenously, it is used in cardiac arrest and certain overdoses (e.g., tricyclic antidepressants).
254	Sodium Chloride	saline,IV fluid,electrolyte,hydration,normal saline	Sodium Chloride (Normal Saline, 0.9%) is an isotonic intravenous solution used for fluid and electrolyte replacement, hydration, and as a vehicle for drug administration. It contains sodium and chloride.
255	Sodium Valproate	anticonvulsant,mood stabilizer,epilepsy,bipolar,migraine	Sodium Valproate (Valproic Acid) is an anticonvulsant used to treat epilepsy (generalized and partial seizures), bipolar disorder (manic episodes), and migraine prevention.
256	Soothing Agent + Local Anaesthetic + Steroid	topical combination,analgesic,corticosteroid,dermatology	This triple-action topical combination contains a soothing agent (e.g., calamine), a local anesthetic (e.g., lidocaine), and a corticosteroid (e.g., hydrocortisone). It is used for inflamed, painful, itchy skin conditions such as hemorrhoids, eczema, and dermatitis.
257	Soothing Agent + Local Anaesthetic	topical combination,analgesic,dermatology,itching,pain	This topical combination contains a soothing agent (e.g., calamine) and a local anesthetic (e.g., lidocaine or benzocaine). It is used to relieve pain, itching, and discomfort from minor skin irritations, insect bites, and sunburn.
258	Spironolactone	potassium-sparing diuretic,aldosterone antagonist,hypertension,heart failure	Spironolactone is a potassium-sparing diuretic and aldosterone antagonist used to treat hypertension, heart failure (especially with reduced ejection fraction), edema, and hyperaldosteronism. It also has anti-androgen effects used in acne and hirsutism.
259	Streptokinase	thrombolytic,fibrinolytic,clot buster,MI,DVT,PE	Streptokinase is a thrombolytic (clot-dissolving) enzyme used to treat acute myocardial infarction (heart attack), deep vein thrombosis (DVT), pulmonary embolism (PE), and arterial thrombosis. It activates plasminogen to plasmin.
260	Sulfasalazine	disease-modifying antirheumatic drug,DMARD,ulcerative colitis,Crohn's	Sulfasalazine is used to treat inflammatory bowel disease (ulcerative colitis and Crohn's disease) and rheumatoid arthritis. It is cleaved in the colon to mesalazine (anti-inflammatory) and sulfapyridine.
261	Tamoxifen	SERM,breast cancer,chemotherapy,estrogen modulator	Tamoxifen is a selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) used to treat hormone receptor-positive breast cancer in premenopausal and postmenopausal women, and for breast cancer prevention in high-risk women.
262	Tamsulosin	alpha blocker,alpha-1 antagonist,BPH,urinary retention	Tamsulosin is an alpha-1 adrenergic antagonist used to treat benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) by relaxing smooth muscle in the prostate and bladder neck, improving urine flow.
263	Terazosin	alpha blocker,antihypertensive,BPH,alpha-1 antagonist	Terazosin is an alpha-1 adrenergic antagonist used to treat hypertension and benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). It relaxes vascular smooth muscle and reduces prostate/bladder outlet resistance.
264	Terbinafine HCl	antifungal,allylamine,dermatophyte,onychomycosis,ringworm	Terbinafine HCl is an allylamine antifungal used to treat dermatophyte infections including onychomycosis (nail fungus), athlete's foot, ringworm, and jock itch. It inhibits squalene epoxidase in fungal cell membranes.
265	Tetracycline	antibiotic,tetracycline,acne,respiratory,cholera	Tetracycline is a broad-spectrum antibiotic used to treat various infections including acne, respiratory tract infections, chlamydia, syphilis, and cholera. It inhibits bacterial protein synthesis.
266	Theophylline	bronchodilator,methylxanthine,asthma,COPD,apnea	Theophylline is a methylxanthine bronchodilator used to treat asthma, COPD, and apnea of prematurity. It relaxes airway smooth muscle and improves diaphragmatic contractility.
267	Thiamine	vitamin B1,thiamine deficiency,beriberi,Wernicke-Korsakoff	Thiamine (Vitamin B1) is used to treat and prevent thiamine deficiency, including beriberi (neurological and cardiovascular symptoms) and Wernicke-Korsakoff syndrome (alcohol-related neurological disorder).
268	Tiabendazole	anthelmintic,antifungal,worm infection,strongyloidiasis	Tiabendazole is an anthelmintic used to treat intestinal worm infections including strongyloidiasis, cutaneous larva migrans, and other nematode infections. It also has some antifungal properties.
269	Timolol Maleate	beta blocker,glaucoma,ophthalmic,antihypertensive	Timolol Maleate is a non-selective beta-blocker used as eye drops to reduce intraocular pressure in glaucoma and ocular hypertension. Oral formulations are used for hypertension and migraine prevention.
270	Tinidazole	antiprotozoal,antibiotic,nitroimidazole,trichomoniasis,giardiasis	Tinidazole is a nitroimidazole antiprotozoal and antibiotic used to treat trichomoniasis, giardiasis, amebiasis, and anaerobic bacterial infections. It has a longer half-life than metronidazole.
271	Tirofiban	antiplatelet,GP IIb/IIIa inhibitor,ACS,cardiology	Tirofiban is a glycoprotein IIb/IIIa inhibitor used intravenously to prevent platelet aggregation in acute coronary syndrome (unstable angina, NSTEMI) and during percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI, angioplasty).
272	Tolbutamide	sulfonylurea,antidiabetic,type 2 diabetes,insulin secretagogue	Tolbutamide is a first-generation sulfonylurea used to treat type 2 diabetes. It stimulates insulin release from pancreatic beta cells. It is less potent than newer sulfonylureas.
273	Tranexamic Acid	antifibrinolytic,hemostatic,heavy bleeding,menorrhagia,trauma	Tranexamic Acid is an antifibrinolytic used to prevent and treat heavy bleeding (menorrhagia, postpartum hemorrhage, trauma, surgery, hemophilia). It blocks plasminogen activation and stabilizes clots.
274	Trihexyphenidyl	anticholinergic,antiparkinson,extrapyramidal,muscarinic antagonist	Trihexyphenidyl is an anticholinergic used to treat Parkinson's disease and drug-induced extrapyramidal symptoms caused by antipsychotics. It restores dopamine-acetylcholine balance in the basal ganglia.
275	Verapamil	calcium channel blocker,antiarrhythmic,antihypertensive,migraine	Verapamil is a non-dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker used to treat hypertension, angina (including vasospastic angina), atrial arrhythmias (atrial fibrillation/flutter), and migraine prevention.
276	Vincristine	chemotherapy,vinca alkaloid,antineoplastic,leukemia,lymphoma	Vincristine is a vinca alkaloid chemotherapy agent used to treat acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL), Hodgkin and non-Hodgkin lymphoma, neuroblastoma, Wilms' tumor, and other childhood cancers. It inhibits microtubule formation.
277	Warfarin	anticoagulant,vitamin K antagonist,blood thinner,DVT,PE,AFib	Warfarin is an oral anticoagulant (vitamin K antagonist) used to prevent and treat deep vein thrombosis (DVT), pulmonary embolism (PE), stroke in atrial fibrillation (AFib), and after heart valve replacement.
278	Water for Injection	sterile water,solvent,diluent,pharmaceutical preparation	Water for Injection (WFI) is sterile, pyrogen-free water used as a solvent and diluent for preparing injectable medications. It is not for direct intravenous infusion without added solutes.
279	Zinc	mineral supplement,zinc deficiency,wound healing,diarrhea,immune	Zinc is an essential mineral used to treat and prevent zinc deficiency. It supports immune function, wound healing, reduces diarrhea severity in children, and is used for Wilson's disease and the common cold (lozenges).
280	5-Fluorouracil	chemotherapy,antimetabolite,pyrimidine antagonist,skin cancer,topical	5-Fluorouracil (5-FU) is an antimetabolite chemotherapy used to treat colorectal cancer, breast cancer, gastric cancer, and other solid tumors. Topically, it is used for actinic keratosis and superficial basal cell carcinoma.
\.
COPY public.investigationparameters (investigationparametersid, investigationparameter, parameterorder, investigationsid) FROM stdin;
\.
COPY public.investigations (investigationsid, investigation, category, investigationtype, levels, labdescription) FROM stdin;
019d8bc3-60dc-7b73-aa87-8069aff2d4bf	C Reactive Protein	Biochemistry	Lab	{B2,C}	Acute phase protein marker for inflammation, infection, and tissue injury.
019d8bc3-60dc-7465-9051-14ed8795da59	2 Hour Post Prandial Blood Glucose	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures blood glucose levels 2 hours after a meal to assess glucose metabolism and diabetes control.
019d8bc3-60dc-756e-a75a-dcb199d7a67b	24 Hr Urine for Protein	Urinalysis	Lab	{A,B1}	Quantifies protein excretion in urine over 24 hours to assess kidney function and detect proteinuria.
019d8bc3-60dc-7589-a54d-d1d167f8d15b	Acid Phosphate	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures acid phosphatase levels in blood, used in detecting prostate cancer and monitoring treatment.
019d8bc3-60dc-759a-99ed-143bc6895a16	AEC	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Absolute Eosinophil Count - measures eosinophil levels to assess allergic conditions and parasitic infections.
019d8bc3-60dc-75a9-8d23-c6fe72e92e36	Apt-Prothrombin Time	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures time taken for blood to clot, used to monitor anticoagulant therapy and detect bleeding disorders.
019d8bc3-60dc-75c6-af10-b95af21a9ba6	B/F for Malaria Parasites	Microbiology	Lab	{A,B1}	Blood film microscopy for detection and quantification of malaria parasites in blood.
019d8bc3-60dc-75da-a5c2-33f0c22a1491	Bleeding and Clotting Time	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Assesses platelet function and coagulation status by measuring time for bleeding to stop and clot to form.
019d8bc3-60dc-75ee-9b2e-1cf06172479e	Blood for C/S	Microbiology	Lab	{A,B1}	Blood culture and sensitivity testing to identify bacterial pathogens and determine antibiotic susceptibility.
019d8bc3-60dc-7606-823f-6f9a1495b5e9	Blood Grouping	Blood Bank	Lab	{A,B1}	Determines ABO and Rh blood group type for blood transfusion compatibility.
019d8bc3-60dc-7614-943d-adc028cb7f3c	Blood Grouping & Antibody Screen	Blood Bank	Lab	{A,B1}	Determines blood group and screens for unexpected red blood cell antibodies before transfusion.
019d8bc3-60dc-7624-bd31-ab4a67ca4aed	Blood Parasites	Microbiology	Lab	{A,B1}	Microscopic examination of blood for parasites including malaria, filaria, and trypanosomes.
019d8bc3-60dc-7639-8e93-6a672ee6d767	Blood Sugar PP	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Post-prandial blood glucose measurement taken 2 hours after a meal to assess glucose regulation.
019d8bc3-60dc-764f-8548-71db1abedb0d	Blood Urea	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures urea nitrogen in blood to assess kidney function and protein metabolism.
019d8bc3-60dc-7662-85d4-5de58141c1b2	Chloride	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures chloride levels in blood to assess electrolyte balance, acid-base disorders, and hydration status.
019d8bc3-60dc-7673-b804-694a5fc581e9	Demonstration of Heinz bodies	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Microscopic detection of Heinz bodies in red blood cells to assess oxidative damage and drug-induced hemolysis.
019d8bc3-60dc-7684-8da0-c02f743b026d	Donor Screening for HB & AG	Blood Bank	Lab	{A,B1}	Screens blood donors for Hepatitis B surface antigen to prevent transmission through transfusion.
019d8bc3-60dc-7697-9c99-89faed6dae0a	ECG	Cardiology	Procedure	{A,B1}	Electrocardiogram records electrical activity of the heart to detect arrhythmias, ischemia, and other cardiac conditions.
019d8bc3-60dc-76ad-b4bb-2f3e6e8f3ea1	Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate (ESR)	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures rate at which red blood cells settle in plasma, indicating inflammation or infection.
019d8bc3-60dc-76c1-86a9-f0554829dde7	Fasting Blood Sugar/Random Blood Sugar	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures blood glucose levels for diabetes diagnosis and monitoring, either after fasting or at any random time.
019d8bc3-60dc-76d7-893e-be413217a456	Grouping/Cross Matching/Unit	Blood Bank	Lab	{A,B1}	Compatibility testing between donor blood and recipient before blood transfusion.
019d8bc3-60dc-76e8-a515-b0b6540e4950	Haemoglobin Estimation (HB)	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures hemoglobin concentration in blood to diagnose and monitor anemia and polycythemia.
019d8bc3-60dc-76fa-a31b-28917bed364f	Hematocrit	Haematology	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures proportion of blood volume occupied by red blood cells, used to diagnose anemia and polycythemia.
019d8bc3-60dc-7708-b932-6677065f00e3	IOPA Xray	Radiology	Imaging	{A,B1}	Intraoral Periapical X-ray for detailed imaging of individual teeth and surrounding bone.
019d8bc3-60dc-771d-9d6b-00ecc373a08f	Malaria Card Test (Dipstik assay/rapid card)	Microbiology	Lab	{A,B1}	Rapid immunochromatographic test for detection of malaria antigens in blood, providing quick results.
019d8bc3-60dc-772d-a038-0b4f28b2e2d3	NA+	Biochemistry	Lab	{A,B1}	Measures sodium levels in blood to assess electrolyte balance, hydration status, and kidney function.
